{"cursor":"6892","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox company\n| company_logo =\n|company_name = 4mm Games, LLC |company_type = LLC |foundation = 2008 |defunct = 2012 \n\n|fate = Dissolved  |location = New York City, New York,\nUSA |key_people = Jamie King, Gary Foreman, Nicholas Perrett, Paul Coyne Matt Martin (2009-08-26) [http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/4mm-games-nicholas-\nperrett \"4mm Games' Nicholas Perrett\"], GamesIndustry.biz. Retrieved 2011-01-\n26. |industry = Video games |products = [[Def Jam Rapstar]],  Dog Show Friends,  Alli\nSkate  }} '4mm Games' was a New York based video game\ndevelopment company founded in 2008 by two founders of\nRockstar Games, Jamie King and Gary Foreman along with former Image Metrics exec\nNicholas Perrett, and Def Jam Enterprises, Warner Music Group and NBC exec Paul\nCoyne. 4mm was founded with the intent of bringing the\nexperience of Constantly Connected Gaming to the next generation of gamers. Konami UK [http://uk.games.konami-europe.com/game.do?idGame=269\n\"Def Jam Rapstar\"], Konami. Retrieved 2011-01-26. OBE and former NCSoft\nCEO Geoff Heath was a member of the advisory board and offers strategic\ninput. Christopher Dring (2010-05-06) [http://www.mcvuk.com/news/38835/Heath-returns-with-4mm-\nGames \"Heath returns with 4mm Games\"], MCV. Retrieved 2011-01-26.\n\nThe company released the Terminal Reality developed and Konami / Autumn Games\npublished Hip-Hop Music game [[Def Jam Rapstar]] on October\n5, 2010, in North America Tom Magrino (2010-07-03)\n[http://www.gamespot.com/xbox360/puzzle/defjamrapstar/news.html?sid=6264522 \"Def\nJam Rapstar dropping in NA October 5\"], Gamespot. Retrieved 2011-01-26.\nand November 26, 2010, in Europe (2010-11-26) [http://www.-\ngamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/65821/MAKE_THE_WORLD_YOUR_STAGE_WITH_DEF_JAM_R-\nAPSTAR.php \"MAKE THE WORLD YOUR STAGE WITH DEF JAM RAPSTAR\"], Gamasutra.\nRetrieved 2011-01-26. for the PlayStation 3, Nintendo Wii, and Xbox 360.\n\n4mm Games also released Dog Show Friends, a Facebook social game based on The\nNational Dog Show Presented by Purina in conjunction with NBC Sports on November\n24, 2010. David Cohen (2010-11-24) [http://www.mediabistro.com/webnewser/nbc-sports-4mm-games-facebook-become-dog-\nshow-friends_b9874 \"NBC Sports, 4mm Games, Facebook Become Dog Show Friends\"],\nGamespot. Retrieved 2011-01-26.\n\nThe company was working with Alli, the Alliance of Action Sports to create new\ndigital titles based on the organizationâs events. The plan was to release games\nbased on sports such as snowboarding, skateboarding and motocross, as well as\nAlli tournaments such as the Dew Tour, Gatorade Free Flow Tour and Winter Dew\nTour. According to 4mm, the games would have provided both âbite sized and fully\nimmersive game play experiencesâ and would be released on a range of platforms,\nincluding mobiles, Smartphones, TV and web browser. James\nBatchelor (2010-06-11) [http://www.mcvuk.com/news/39415/4mm-to-enter-Action-Sports-\nmarket \"4mm to enter Action Sports market\"], MCV. Retrieved 2011-01-26.\nThe first of these games was to have been a free-to-play browser-based\nskateboarding game called Alli Skate. Garrett Estrada (2010-10-\n21) [http://unlvrebelyell.com/2010/10/21/%E2%80%9C4mm%E2%80%9D-reveals-new-game-at-\ndew-tour-skate-finals/ \"4mm reveals new game at Dew Tour skate finals\"], The\nRebel Yell. Retrieved 2011-01-26.\n","linknr":172,"url":"4mm_Games","recorded":1375074855,"links":["/w/index.php?title=4mm_Games&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=4mm_Games&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki